  "answer": "ABCDE) All of these are at least partially correct. It is not clear whether weight loss of 10% or 15% is the required threshold, but it certainly is close. Serum albumin of less than 3 gm per 100 ml. remains the most constant identiﬁer of patients at risk in the literature and has been so for years. Global asses",
