  "specialty": "Review",
  "difficulty": "Medium",
  "markdown_debrief": "### SHARP 4.0 Cognitive & Surgical Debrief\n\n> **💡 Cells stick, seal, and signal with specialized junctions!**\n\n---\n\n## S — Set the Stage\nThis question correctly identifies key characteristics of various cell junctions. Tight junctions form selective permeability barriers, desmosomes provide strong cell-to-cell adhesion, and gap junctions facilitate direct cell communication.\n\n## H — Highlight Excellence\nCell junctions are fundamental to tissue integrity and function, classifying into occluding, anchoring, and communicating types. Tight junctions (zonula occludens) are crucial for epithelial barrier function, preventing paracellular diffusion by forming a belt near the apical pole. Desmosomes are 'spot welds' that anchor intermediate filaments, providing robust mechanical strength between cells. Gap junctions, composed of connexons, allow for rapid electrical and chemical signaling between adjacent cells, essential for coordinated tissue responses.\n\n## A — Address the Gaps\n\nOption B (Incorrect): Tight junctions are typically located near the apical pole of the cell, not the basal pole. They form a complete belt around the cell, regulating paracellular transport and maintaining cell polarity.\n\n## R — Review Learning Points\n\n| Junction Type | Primary Function | Key Feature |\n|---|---|---|\n| Tight Junction (Zonula Occludens) | Occluding/Barrier | Apical location, forms belt, prevents paracellular diffusion |\n| Desmosome (Macula Adherens) | Anchoring/Adhesion | Button-like, anchors intermediate filaments, strong cell-cell attachment |\n| Gap Junction | Communication | Connexons, allows direct electrical/chemical coupling |\n| Adherens Junction (Zonula Adherens) | Anchoring/Adhesion | Belt-like, anchors actin filaments, links cells mechanically |\n\n## P — Plan (Board Pearl)\nBoard Pearl: Tight junctions seal, desmosomes weld, gap junctions talk.\n\n---\n\n## 🔬 Imaging & Intraoperative Pearl\nNo specific imaging or intraoperative pearl applies directly to this basic science question on cell junctions.\n\n## 📋 Guideline Anchor\nNo specific surgical guideline applies to this fundamental cell biology concept.\n\n---\n\n### Answer Breakdown\n| Option | Text | Status |\n|--------|------|--------|\n| A | The major occluding junction is the tight junction or zonula occludens | ❌ Incorrect |\n| B | Tight junctions are usually located near the basal pole of the cell | ❌ Incorrect |\n| C | Desmosomes are button-like points of attachment which serve to weld togethe | ❌ Incorrect |\n| D | Gap junctions are a type of cell junction specialized for cell communicatio | ❌ Incorrect |\n\n**✅ Answer: a, c, d) Cell junctions are classiﬁed as occluding, anchoring, and communicating. The major occluding junctio** &nbsp;|&nbsp; **Difficulty: Medium** &nbsp;|&nbsp; **Source: 644827546-General-Surgery-MCQ.txt**\n",
